node.title: COVID cases in NSW reach three-month high after 1,360 new infections recorded
node.description: Health authorities in NSW confirm 1,360 cases of COVID-19 in the 24 hours to 8:00pm yesterday, as a cluster in Newcastle grows and the Premier delays a press conference on the virus.
node.content: ["NSW recorded 1,360 new COVID-19 infections in the 24 hours to 8:00pm yesterday.", "It\u2019s the highest number of new infections since September 11.", "One new death was recorded in the reporting period.", "Premier Dominic Perrottet had been due to front the cameras for a COVID-19 briefing at 9:00am today with Health Minister Brad Hazzard and Chief Health Officer Kerry Chant.", "However, that press conference has since been delayed until 12:00pm.", "There are 166 people in hospital, including 24 in intensive care.\u00a0", "Mr Hazzard yesterday\u00a0ruled out any snap lockdowns or delaying today\u2019s easing of restrictions, despite a big jump in cases yesterday.", "A total of 804 new cases were recorded in the 24 hours to 8pm on Monday, 21 of which were the Omicron variant.", "A COVID-19 cluster linked to a Newcastle nightclub continues to drive infections.", "So far, more than 200 people who attended a The Argyle Club late on Wednesday night and early on Thursday morning last week have tested positive for the virus.", "NSW Health believes there were between 650 and 680 people at\u00a0the venue.\u00a0", "A total of\u00a094.8\u00a0per cent\u00a0of people aged 16\u00a0and over\u00a0have had one dose of a COVID-19 vaccine, while\u00a093.2\u00a0per cent\u00a0of people in the same age group have had two doses of a COVID-19 vaccine.\u00a0", "More to come."]
